  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast and half board dinners are served in the <strong>Restaurant Panoramasaal</strong>. Enjoy a beautiful view of Klosters and far out into Prättigau. Breakfast is continental, with soft-boiled eggs available. Additional cooked items can be ordered (payable locally).</p>
<p>The half board evening meal is four delicious courses with a choice of main, and the menu changes daily. Complimentary tap water is served during meal times.</p>
<p>The hotel also has two à la carte restaurants if you fancy a treat. Enjoy candlelight dinners and a range of classic and international dishes in the cosy <strong>Bündner Stübli</strong>. There's also the hotel's excellent raclette stübli - <strong>Casetta Allegra</strong>.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <cateringShortDescription></cateringShortDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>This comfortable hotel has a reputation for outstanding hospitality and facilities. Conveniently located, it's approximately a 15-minute walk from the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/5cdc3bd60ed74827b457178da3c4090e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5cdc3bd60ed74827b457178da3c4090e}" title="Klosters">Klosters</a>. There's also a bus that stops just 40 metres away, providing easy access to the centre and the Madrisa and Gotschna gondolas.</p>
<h2>An excellent choice for families</h2>
<p>Teenagers are in for a treat with a range of activities to enjoy, including mini golf, outdoor tennis courts, and a sports hall. For younger kids, there's a dedicated play area, an indoor paddling pool, and even a petting zoo.</p>
<p>Adults, you're not forgotten - there's ample opportunity for a little R&amp;R. Take a well-deserved dip in the indoor pool, followed by five minutes peace in the sauna. As the day of adventure winds down, you can enjoy a quiet drink on the terrace and soak in the spectacular views.</p>]]></description>
